snippet.title: Dilli Ki Winters | The Paayal Jain
snippet.description:
Hey Guys , 
Hope you enjoy this winter video . We love you so much .

Click on Link To Buy Himalaya Serum - https://amzn.to/3EaXbc2

This video shows different behaviours of Indians during winters . Dilli Ki Winters is extreme .  This is a very comic and relatable video. When the temperature is falling and the heaters , hot water bags , heating pads , sweaters , sweatshirts , hoodies , coats , jackets , scarfs mufflers , gloves , thermals , socks , monkey caps , boots , comes to beat the cold especially if it's delhi winters . College exams during winters , School Board Exams with hot coffee or tea travelling by metro bikes in thand , shopping from sarojini market for latest winter fashion , planning winter trip to hills with friends to see snow , cause snowfall , bonfire with friends is the best time . indian moms covering kids in multiple layers of warm clothes to avoid cold and flue , Feeding winter green leafy vegetables , hara saag and  enjoying thand me gajar ka halwa , lazy winters in bed watching shows Tv serials anupama or christmas movies with hot chocolate , chai , heater , blanket perfect cosy environment .  Buying school winter uniform for kids , Mothers and their millions of excuses when it comes to exercising or changing life in sardiyan that sardi bht pad rhi he and alot more . All these winter problems that we all indians in winters face .

This video is filled with such memories and situations we all have been in. 
Relish and Relive your Memories.. You will love this .

Vallavanukku Pullum Aayudham  is a 2014 Indian Tamil-language action comedy film directed by Srinath and released by Studio Green on 9 May 2014. A remake of S. S. Rajamouli's successful Telugu film Maryada Ramanna (2010) which was based on Buster Keaton's Our Hospitality (1923),[1] the film was jointly produced by PVP Cinema and Santhanam, who also played the lead role in it, alongside newcomer Ashna Zaveri. 7th Sky Entertainment‚Äôs highly anticipated mega signature project, Sunn Mere Dil, is the most awaited drama serial. The mega drama boasts a star-studded cast led by Wahaj Ali and Maya Ali. Written by the renowned Khalil Ur Rehman Qamar and directed by the acclaimed Haseeb Hasan, Sunn Mere Dil promises to be a one-of-a-kind drama.

Sunn Mere Dil is a tale in which love finds a new meaning, where one person‚Äôs devotion quietly flourishes, often unnoticed. Their heart beats for someone who may never truly understand the depth of their feelings. Yet, in their silent sacrifices, they realize that true love is not about
possession but about selflessness.

Every unspoken gesture and unseen act of kindness brings them fulfillment, as they put their beloved‚Äôs happiness above their own, showing that love is not just about being together, it‚Äôs about redefining happiness, even at the expense of their contentment.

snippet.title: Anuv Jain - AFSOS ft. AP Dhillon (Official Visualizer)
snippet.description:
Listen to Anuv Jain - 'Afsos' ft. AP Dhillon on all streaming platforms - https://umgindia.lnk.to/Afsos
#anuvjain #afsos #apdhillon 

For inquiries - anuvjain.work@gmail.com
Instagram - @anuvjain
Manager- aayushman@representmgmt.in

Audio Credits:
Composer: Anuv Jain, Shinda Kahlon, AP Dhillon
Lyrics: Anuv Jain, Shinda Kahlon, AP Dhillon, Reeka Jain
Music Producers: Angad Bahra, Anuv Jain, Luca Mauti, AP Dhillon, Brendan Rogers
Atmos Mix: Pixl

Project Managers - Aayushman Sinha, Tanvi Seth, Sidhantha Jain, Murtuza Gadiwala, Madhura Rumde, Anirudh Voletti
Team: Shirsodhi Banerjee, Mihika Bansal, Bhavya Killa

Lyric Video by Hariom Verma (LazyOm)
Special Mention to the team at Dreaming in Digital

Artwork: Kartik Kher, LazyOm, AK Digitals
Shout Out to Fleck Media for capturing an incredible moment

AFSOS (Lyrics)

A 1

Haan 
Teri yaadan yaadan 
Teri yaadan le ke betha 
Kai raatan raatan

Par aaj
Ena raatan picho
Meinu sab sach nazar ae aunda
Kivein akhan akhan?

B 1

Jo guroor si 
Oh fizool si 
Meinu aaj pata laga 
Ki kasoor si 

Mere dil de noor 
Main si mash-hoor 
Tenu karta dur 
Oh, bekasoor!

Kinj gairan nu 
Main apna mann 
Mileya mere apne nu 
Gair ban

Eh taan zaroor 
Dil karta choor
Tera

C 1 

Te haan
Main duniya vekhi 
Tere dil nu vekh na paya 
Main jhalla jhalla 

Karda si
Wadeya nawan di
Gallan gallan

Hun ethe
Marda janda 
Main kalla kalla

A 2

Hun kyun 
Afsos hoya?
Hun ki fayeda?
Milna ni
Je chahaan chahaan

Main hun
Ghadiya de hath te
Kivein modha 
Rukh samay da 
Te rahaan rahaan?

D 

Chand pal do pal 
Teri sunda battan je 

Tere nal hi 
Sab katda rattan je 

Tere hanju dekhda 
Vich barsattan je

Kitte karda teh 
Eh dil di vattan je 

B 2

Kaisi shaam si
Tere naam si 
Jo padheya na main
Ki pegham si?

Main hairan si
Naadan si
Kis gallon meri jaan
Pareshan si?

Tenu hasde vekh ke
Baar baar
Tenu puchi na main kadey tere
Dil di saar

Tera intezar, 
Meri samjho baar 
Kidda katey ne tu din metho 
Haar haar?

C 2

Haan
Jo pyaar si tera
Thoda vi samajh na paya 
Main jhalla jhalla 

Haan
Eh dil pachtave 
Tere bin hun reh na pave 
Eh kalla kalla

A 3

Hun kyun 
Afsos hoya?
Hun ki fayeda?
Milna ni
Je chahaan chahaan

Main hun
Ghadiya de hath te
Kivein modha 
Rukh samay da 
Te rahaan rahaan?

Te rahaan rahaan
Te rahaan rahaan

snippet.title: SNAIL FRY | NATHAI VARUVAL | Snail Recipe Cooking and Eating in Village | Healthy Village Recipes
snippet.description:
Discover the art of traditional Snail Fry (Nathai Varuval) cooking in the heart of the village! üêå‚ú® This unique recipe combines fresh, locally sourced snails with a blend of aromatic spices, creating a mouthwatering dish that‚Äôs as healthy as it is flavorful.

Watch as we prepare this delicacy from scratch, using simple yet time-tested techniques over a firewood stove. Every step showcases the charm of village cooking, from cleaning the snails to frying them to perfection.

What‚Äôs in the Recipe:

Fresh snails straight from nature
A medley of traditional spices
Gingelly oil and hand-ground masala for authentic flavor

This video is not just about cooking; it celebrates culture, community, and the joy of sharing delicious food. Stay until the end for a delightful tasting session that will leave you craving this wholesome delicacy!

#AjithKumar #Dubai24H #RacingVictory #AjithKumarRacing #Pathikichu #vidaamuyarchi #MotivationalMusic #NeverGiveUp #Perseverance #sonymusicsouth

This victory is set to the backdrop of Ajith‚Äôs upcoming film Vidamuyarchi, with the motivational track Pathikichu fueling the energy and inspiring everyone who believes in pushing through all obstacles. About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

This channel is owned, operated, and managed by, Contagious Online Media Network Private Limited.

Medical school aspirants know the grind like no one else. From **NEET prep** to the **MBBS dream**, the journey is anything but easy. It starts with endless hours of **study grind**, flipping through **NCERT Bible** pages, and juggling between **mock test anxiety** and **last-minute revision**. The **topper mindset** isn‚Äôt just about getting high scores; it‚Äôs about surviving the **coaching life**, decoding **mnemonics & shortcuts**, and finding ways to stay motivated despite the sleepless nights. Every medical aspirant has promised themselves **"Kal se serious"** at least once, only to be distracted by **procrastination**, the eternal enemy of every student. But when the dream is to wear that **white coat** and hold a **stethoscope**, there‚Äôs no room for giving up.  

The real adventure begins when you step into **medical college**, where the excitement of the **first dissection** is mixed with the terror of **viva** exams. Walking into the **anatomy lab struggles** feels like entering an unknown world, and **cadaver room stories** are enough to haunt even the bravest students. Then comes the **8 AM lectures**, where half the class is either sleeping or relying on **coffee-fueled nights** to stay awake. But nothing prepares you for the **36-hour shifts** of clinical rotations, where exhaustion meets **ward duty blues**, and the real learning begins. **Sleep vs. study dilemma** becomes an everyday battle, and some days, **mental breakdowns before exams** feel inevitable.  

Yet, amidst all the chaos, **study group saviors** make the journey bearable. There‚Äôs always that one friend who calls during **exam panic mode**, asking **"Bhai tune kya padha?"**, as if cramming last minute will change fate. **Late-night library sessions** turn into deep discussions about life, and **seniors vs. juniors bonding** happens over shared struggles and survival tips. Even the **professors‚Äô legendary one-liners** become inside jokes among students. And despite the stress, **college fests & stress relief** moments remind every medical student why they chose this path in the first place.  

But medical school isn‚Äôt just about books and tests‚Äîit‚Äôs also about expectations. **Parents‚Äô expectations** loom large, with the constant reminder of **"Doctor ban jao, phir aish hi aish"**, while reality proves otherwise. The fear of **imposter syndrome** creeps in, making students question if they truly belong here. Some dream of the day they‚Äôll finally attend **convocation day**, while others are just trying to get through the next **clinical rotation** without passing out from exhaustion. The road to becoming a doctor is paved with challenges, but the **determination to achieve it** keeps every medical aspirant going.  

Because at the end of the day, it‚Äôs not just about **cracking NEET** or surviving **medical textbooks overload**‚Äîit‚Äôs about the passion to heal, the courage to face setbacks, and the resilience to keep going. Whether it‚Äôs the struggle of remembering every tiny detail from **pharmacology** or the joy of finally making sense of **pathology**, every step in this journey shapes the future **doctors of tomorrow**. So to every **medical school aspirant** out there, battling through **NCERT Bible**, surviving **mock test anxiety**, and chasing that **MBBS dream**‚Äîyou‚Äôre not alone. The struggle is real, but so is the reward. Keep going! üí™üöÄ

he masala tea? Too watered down. The cheese omelette? A bit eggy at first but got better. The hara bhara kebab? Surprisingly soft and moist. The baked beans? Classic, soft, and mushy.

snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi

snippet.description:
India celebrates the 76th Republic Day on 26th January 2025. We at Doordarshan extend our warm regards to all Indians in the country as well as abroad. It is the proud privilege of Doordarshan, India's National Broadcaster to LIVE-STREAM the magnificent 76th Republic Day Parade on our official channel on YouTube. www.youtube/DoordarshanNational. Doordarshan has been telecasting the Republic Day Parade LIVE since the early sixties when cameras and equipment had to be taken out of the existing studio for this event! Today, for the tenth consecutive year, we will LIVE-STREAM the Republic Day Parade. Proud Indians and Indophiles from all over the world will be watching, along with our viewers from the freezing climate of Leh to the remotest corners of Kanyakumari, Thank you for always being with us - Friends of Doordarshan. We at Doordarshan extend our warm regards to all Indians in the country as well as abroad. It is the proud privilege of Doordarshan.

How to make canteen style toast sandwich recipe / toast sandwich recipe 

How to make Sandwich Chutney-
In a mixer grinder, add garlic, ginger, coriander, green chilies, mint leaves, lemon juice,bread pieces, chat masala, salt cold water , and churn it well. Don't make it too watery.¬†

Sandwich Stuffing-¬†
In a mixing bowl, add finely chopped onions, carrots, capsicum, add the chutney we made, 1 cup grated cheese, and mix well.¬†

For Sandwich-
Apply soft butter on bread, add the stuffing and spread it evenly. keep another slice of bread on top of it.¬†
Heat the grill pan, apply butter , keep the sandwich & cook until it turns crispy.¬†

How to make canteen style toast sandwich recipe / toast sandwich recipe 

How to make Sandwich Chutney-
In a mixer grinder, add garlic, ginger, coriander, green chilies, mint leaves, lemon juice,bread pieces, chat masala, salt cold water , and churn it well. Don't make it too watery.¬†

Sandwich Stuffing-¬†
In a mixing bowl, add finely chopped onions, carrots, capsicum, add the chutney we made, 1 cup grated cheese, and mix well.¬†

For Sandwich-
Apply soft butter on bread, add the stuffing and spread it evenly. keep another slice of bread on top of it.¬†
Heat the grill pan, apply butter , keep the sandwich & cook until it turns crispy.¬†
